<br>
Personally, I think you it would be worthwhile finding similar boards (one totally unmoderated, one partially moderated etc.) to review what has been tried, what seems to work or not--apply what you find to what you want to achieve here, and then talk to the mod's of the boards that have achieved something of what you desire here, to get their thoughts on how much moderating they do, how many people per forum etc.<br>
<br>
<br>
If that is too much trouble to research it, then perhaps you can try having one truly unmoderated "Rant at Your Own Risk" forum and have a "Debate" forum which is moderated (no personal attacks, guild attacks, trolling posts, etc.)<br>
<br>
My guess is in a few months time you will see more hits on a moderated Debate forum than you will the unmoderated rant forum as most people want to read something that stimulates their minds more than they want to read someone's trolling trash talk.  Both sides are happy this way.<br>
<br>
Put up some well defined rules for the Debate Forum and disclaimer on the rant forum that all posts within can contain subjective unvalidated material (i.e. vulgarity, sexually explicit language, personal attacks, etc.) which is not moderated and will in all liklihood be highly offensive to sensitive readers.<br>
<br>
anyway that's my 2 copperpieces<br>
